1-10-19',4,0,7.7,'https://github.com/xiaojiangxl/CVE-2021-21234'),('CVE-2021-27905','The ReplicationHandler (normally registered at \"/replication\" under a Solr core) in Apache Solr has a \"masterUrl\" (also \"leaderUrl\" alias) parameter that is used to designate another ReplicationHandler on another Solr core to replicate index data into the local core. To prevent a SSRF vulnerability, Solr ought to check these parameters against a similar configuration it uses for the \"shards\" parameter. Prior to this bug getting fixed, it did not. This problem affects essentially all Solr versions prior to it getting fixed in 8.8.2.','2021-08-10',7.5,9.8,0,'https://github.com/murataydemir/CVE-2021-27905'),('CVE-2021-29447','Wordpress is an open source CMS. A user with the ability to upload files (like an Author) can exploit an XML parsing issue in the Media Library leading to XXE attacks. This requires WordPress installation to be using PHP 8. Access to internal files is possible in a successful XXE attack. This has been patched in WordPress version 5.7.1, along with the older affected versions via a minor release. We strongly recommend you keep auto-updates enabled.','2022-11-14',4,6.5,7.1,'https://github.com/mega8bit/exploit_cve-2021-29447'),('CVE-2021-40346','An integer overflow exists in HAProxy 2.0 through 2.5 in htx_add_header that can be exploited to perform an HTTP request smuggling attack, allowing an attacker to bypass all configured http-request HAProxy ACLs and possibly other ACLs.','2021-09-10',5,7.5,0,'https://github.com/alikarimi999/CVE-2021-40346'),('CVE-2021-39433','A local file inclusion (LFI) vulnerability exists in version BIQS IT Biqs-drive v1.83 and below when sending a specific payload as the file parameter to download/index.php. This allows the attacker to read arbitrary files from the server with the permissions of the configured web-user.','2021-10-04',5,7.5,0,'https://github.com/PinkDraconian/CVE-2021-39433'),('CVE-2021-46702','Tor Browser 9.0.7 on 